# Design System Rules

## Design Source

Figma is the source of truth for visual values:

- spacing, typography, color, component variants

Never invent visual values. Map Figma output to project tokens.

## Design Tokens

Import tokens via `packages/ui-react/src/styles/tokens.css`:

```css
@import "@idenflu/ui-foundations/css/tokens-light.css";
@import "@idenflu/ui-foundations/css/tokens-dark.css";
```

- Use CSS custom properties from `@idenflu/ui-foundations` only
- Never hardcode colors, spacing, or typography values

## Component API

Reference Material UI and Carbon React for API shape and behavior.

Follow:

- composable / slot-based architecture when needed
- controlled and uncontrolled patterns
- accessibility first

Do not copy MUI or Carbon APIs verbatim. Adapt to idenflu naming and tokens.

## Accessibility

Every component must:

- support keyboard interaction
- support screen readers
- expose appropriate ARIA attributes

## TypeScript

- strict typing, no `any`
- export public types from component `index.ts` and `packages/ui-react/src/index.ts`

## Documentation

For every component provide:

- props interface
- Storybook stories (`*.stories.tsx`)
- accessibility notes in stories or component comments
